    "question_id" : 2329358,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In the spirit of Stack Overflow being <a href=\"https://www.joelonsoftware.com/2008/09/15/stack-overflow-launches/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">a combination of Reddit and Wikipedia</a>, here's some additional information, which is relevant to the question, and can also be an answer to the question.</p>\n<p>When you ask NetBeans IDE to create a missing implementation, it uses an <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/UnsupportedOperationException.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><strong>UnsupportedOperationException</strong></a>:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>void setPropertiesWithReader(IDataReader rdr)\n{\n   throw new UnsupportedOperationException(&quot;Not supported yet.&quot;); // Generated from nbfs://nbhost/SystemFileSystem/Templates/Classes/Code/GeneratedMethodBody\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>If it's good enough for NetBeans, it's good enough for us.</p>\n"
  } ],
